FREE State cops have arrested four people after the discovery of the body of a 75-year-old madala in his house in Brandfort. According to spokesman Captain Stephen Thakeng, on Thursday, 19 January, a domestic worker alerted the police to the gruesome discovery. “The deceased was found in a pool of blood. He sustained a wound to his head, and it is suspected that a blunt object was used. Emergency Medical Service personnel were called to the scene, where he was certified dead.” Thakeng added that a case of murder was registered, following which a house was identified in Majwemasweu where three suspects and the owner, a traditional healer, were found. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments “The house was searched and a cellphone belonging to the deceased as well as an unlicensed gun were found and seized. The traditional healer was found in possession of the unlicensed firearm,” he said. The suspects, aged 21, 23, 31 and 38, are facing charges of possession of an unlicensed firearm and murder. They will appear in the Brandfort Magistrates Court on Monday, 23 January.